Row-Level Export Hooks - Modify entire row of data for specific channels:

REAL-WORLD EXAMPLE: Dynamic availability_date based on stock status (Google Shopping):

add_filter('wt_batch_product_export_row_data_google', function($row, $product) {
    if (!isset($row['availability_date'])) {
        return $row;
    }

    $stock_status = $product->get_stock_status();
    if ('onbackorder' === $stock_status) {
        // Set to current date + 14 days for backorder
        $row['availability_date'] = gmdate('c', strtotime('+14 days'));
    } elseif ('instock' === $stock_status) {
        // Leave empty for in-stock
        $row['availability_date'] = '';
    }

    return $row;
}, 10, 2);

Hook Pattern: wt_batch_product_export_row_data_{channel}

Available for all channels (google, facebook, pinterest, tiktok, bing, twitter, etc.):
- wt_batch_product_export_row_data_google($row, $product) - Google Shopping
- wt_batch_product_export_row_data_facebook($row, $product) - Facebook/Instagram
- wt_batch_product_export_row_data_pinterest($row, $product) - Pinterest

Parameters:
- $row (array): Complete row data with all mapped fields
- $product (WC_Product|WC_Product_Variation): Product object

Use Cases:
- Conditional field values based on product properties
- Complex pricing or date logic
- Dynamic modifications across multiple fields
- Stock status-based calculations
